docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, Feb. 28. -- Mrs. Hoover received today the members of the Committee on Mobilization of Relief in Welfare and several small delegations, including a group of Congressional callers. Late in the afternoon she drove out for a farewell visit at the home of Mr. and Mrs. French Strother in Wesley Heights.

docs.lead_paragraph: NORTHAMPTON, Mass., March 9. -- Delegates from twenty-seven New England colleges and universities arrived here today for the annual session of the New England Model League of Nations. The attention of the delegates was somewhat divided between the world problems they are to discus and the "frozen" condition of their assets.
